## Spell Descriptions

### Absorb Spell
*2nd level Abjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 Reaction (When targeted by a spell that deals damage)
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
___

A barrier of magical energy appears and protects you. The barrier absorbs 1d10 + your spellcasting ability modifier damage from the spell. If you reduce the spells damage to 0 with this, you gain advantage on the first spell attack you make next turn.

***At Higher Levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the shield increases by 1d10 damage for each level above 2nd.

### Analyze Blood
*1st level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 Action [Ritual]
- **Range:** Touch
- **Components:** V, S, M *(A drop of fresh blood or dried blood no more than a month old.)*
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
___

You read the necromantic energy trapped in blood like a book. You immediately learn whether you have analyzed blood from the same creature before and when the last time you analyzed the blood was. You may only use the blood from a single creature for the material component of this spell. The information in mingled blood is too muddied to be of use. 

***At Higher Levels:*** You may gain additional information from the blood you analyze by channeling more energy into the spell. The additional information you can gain is listed below. You gain all of the information provided by lower levels of the spell as well as the information provided by the spell level you chose.
___
- **2nd** - You know the creature who shed the blood's type(s). (Monstrosity, Undead, Humanoid, etc.)
- **3rd** - You know if the blood carries any diseases or poisons. You also know if the blood is acceptable for transfusion into another creature.
- **4th** - You know if the creature whose blood you used is still alive.
- **5th** - You know the creature's name (if applicable. Creatures with secret names such as Devils cannot have their secret name revealed with this spell.), age, and alignment.
- **6th** - You know whether the creature is on the same plane of existence as you at the time the spell is cast.
- **7th** - You know the approximate location of the creature with a margin of error of one mile.
- **8th** - You have the memories of the creature for the last 12 hours prior to the blood being spilled.
- **9th** - You have the memories of the creature for the last 24 hours prior to the blood being spilled.
___

### Army of the dead
*5th-level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** Self (40 foot radius)
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** 1 minute
___

You raise all corpses within 40 feet of you into ghouls. If there are no corpses around or not enough for the spell the remaining ghouls are conjured, rising up from the ground around you if possible. 

You may raise a number of ghouls equal to your Proficiency bonus + Charisma modifier. These ghouls will perform any command you give to the best of their ability, even sacrificing themselves, until you give them another command. In combat, the ghouls always act during your turn, either before or after your actions as you choose, When either the spell effect ends or they die they will fall apart and turn into dust.

You can only use this spell once per Short or long rest.

### Aura of Infirmity
*3rd-level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 Action
- **Range:** Self (30-foot radius)
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___

Deathly energy radiates from you in an aura with a 30-foot radius.

\pagebreakNum

Until the spell ends, the aura moves with you, centered on you. You can use a bonus action to cause one undead in the aura (including you) to regain 2d6 hit points.

### Aura of Pollution
*4th-level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 Action
- **Range:** Self (30-foot radius)
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes
___

Polluting energy radiates from you in an aura with a 30-foot radius.

Until the spell ends, the aura moves with you, centered on you. Each nonhostile creature in the aura (including you) can’t become diseased, loses any resistance to poison damage, and has disadvantage on saving throws against effects that cause any of the following conditions: blnded, charmed, deafended, frightened, paralyzed, poisoned, and stunned.

### Blood Bath
*2nd-level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 Action
- **Range:** 120 ft
- **Components:** V, S, M *(a drop of blood)
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
___

One creature that you can see must make a Constitution saving throw. If the saving throw fails, the creature suffers 3d8 necrotic damage and is blinded for 1 round as blood spurts from its eyes, ears, mouth, and nose. If the saving throw succeeds, it takes half damage and is not blinded.

### Blood Boil
*2nd-level necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** 20 feet
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
___

You cause the blood of nearby enemies to boil. Any number of creatures of your choice within 20 feet must make a Constitution saving throw. Each target takes 3d6 fire damage, or half on a successful save. Creatures without blood are immune to this power.

***At Higher Levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 3rd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 2nd.

### Blood Parasite
*3rd-level conjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 20 feet
- **Components:** V, S, M (a dessicated parasite, such as a leech)
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___

You infect a creature within range with blood parasites that slowly eat away at it from the inside. At the beginning of each of the infected creature’s turns, it makes a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, it takes 3d8 necrotic damage and you gain hit points equal to half the damage dealt. On a successful save, the effect ends.

### Blood Puppet
*2nd level necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 60 ft
- **Components:** V, S
- ***Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___

You take forceful control over the blood of a target within range. The target you choose must make a Constitution save or have their blood contorted to your will. When you cast this spell, and as an action afterward, you can designate a direction or a physical action for the creature to follow, which it must make to the best of its ability. 

As a bonus action, you can contort the victim’s blood, causing 2d6 necrotic damage. On their turn an affected creature must make a Strength check or be unable to move; if they succeed, their movement is reduced by half. Affected creatures may make an additional Constitution save at the end of their turn, ending the effect on a success. Creatures lacking blood, such as constructs, or certain undead, are immune to this spell.

***At Higher Levels.***  Casting this spell using a spell slot of 4th or higher allows you to target one additional creature per slot.

### Bone Shard
*1st level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 Action
- **Range:** 30 ft
- **Componenets:** V, S, M (Fragments of bone from a corpse)
- **Duration:** Instantaneous

This spell uses the skeletal remains of a corpse to create a projectile weapon. Choose the corpse of a creature within range. Fragments of bones from the corpse splinter off and fly toward another selected target within range. On a successful ranged spell attack, the target takes 2d8 damage, half necrotic, half piercing (rounded up for necrotic damage).

The corpse a small creature has enough material to cast Bone Shard 1d4 times before deteriorating beyond use. Larger creatures provide an additional 1d4 uses per size category greater than small. The caster of the spell must have knowledge of a corpse's location to be used to cast the spell. Corpses in hard cover such as an enclosed coffin, a block of ice,  or buried in mud cannot be used. Corpses buried in soft cover such as loose soil, shallow water, or an open sarcophagus can be used.

**At Higher Levels.** At 2nd level or higher, you may make an additional ranged spell attack when you cast this spell for each slot level above 1st. You can attack the same or a new target. Each additional attack requires a use of material from a corpse.

\pagebreakNum

### Conjure Gargoyle
*4th-level conjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 minute
- **Range:** 90 feet
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 hour
___

You summon a gargoyle under your control in an unoccupied spaces that you can see within range. The gargoyle summoned by this spell crumbles to dust when it drops to 0 hit points or when the spell ends.

The summoned creature is friendly to you and your companions. Roll initiative for the summoned creature, which has its own turns. It obeys any verbal commands that you issue to it (no action required by you). If you don’t issue any commands to it, it defends itself from hostile creatures, but otherwise take no actions.

See the Appendix or the Wacraft Manual of Monsters for the gargoyle’s statistics. 

### Corpse Explosion
*1st-level necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 120 ft range
- **Components:** V, S, M *(a corpse, destroyed upon casting)*
- **Duration:** instantaneous
___

The corpse of a recently deceased creature rapidly bloats at your command and erupts in a gruesome explosion. You target the corpse of a creature that's been dead for no longer than 1 minute that you can see within range, detonating it. 

Each creature within a 5-foot-radius sphere centered on that corpse must make a Dexterity saving throw. A target takes 2d8 necrotic damage on a failed save, or half as much damage on a successful one. The size of the explosion increases by 5 feet for every size larger than Medium.

A corpse detonated this way is destroyed and cannot be raised or resurrected by any ability that requires a complete corpse.

***At Higher Levels.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d8 for each slot level above 1st.

### Dancing Rune Weapon
*5th-level evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** S, M (a small bone replica of a weapon worth at least 200 gp)
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes
___

You create a floating, spectral weapon identical to one that you are wielding that floats alongside you, mimicing your actions. Whenever you take an Attack action, the floating weapon makes an identical attack against either the same target or another within range. Treat this as if you had made another attack with the weapon you are wielding.

\columnbreak

### Death and Decay
*5th-level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 120 ft
- **Components:** V, S, M *(A dead rose)*
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___

You invoke the concept of entropy and decay, causing creatures and objects to wither and rapidly age. A 30-ft radius circle of runes comes into being at a point you choose in range. Creatures in this area of effect when it comes into being or who start their turn in the circle must make a Constitution save or take 3d10 points of necrotic damage, half on a successful save. Undead do not take damage from this spell.

Additionally, the decaying energy invigorates you. While in the area of effect, you have advantage on attack rolls.

Nonmagical plants and creatures in the area don't make saving throws against this spell; they simply wither and die. Corpses in the area decay into skeletons.

### Festering Wounds
*1st level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 Bonus Action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___

Your runes empower your strikes with filth. Until the spell ends, your weapon attacks deal and extra 1d4 necrotic damage on a hit.

### Frozen Strike
*1st level conjuration*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 Bonus Action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___

The next time you hit a creature with a weapon attack before this spell ends, a mass of ice appears at the point of impact, and the target must succeed on a Strength saving throw or be restrained by the magical ice until the spell ends. A Large or larger creature has advantage on this saving throw. If the target succeeds on the save, the ice melts away.

While restrained by this spell, the target takes 1d6 cold damage at the start of each of its turns. A creature restrained by the ice or one that can touch the creature can use its action to make a Strength check against your spell save DC. On a success, the target is freed. 

***At higher level.*** If you cast this spell using a spell slot of 2nd level or higher, the damage increases by 1d6 for each slot level above 1st.

\pagebreakNum

### Heart Strike
*3rd level divination*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** 1 round
___

You infuse your weapon with death energy, causing it to seek out vital points and weaknesses in your foes. The next time you hit a creature with a melee weapon attack before this spell ends, that attack becomes a critical hit, and ignores any resistance or damage resistance (but not immunity) that the target has.

### Icebound Fortitude
*2nd level transmutation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** 1 round
___

You freeze your blood in your veins. Until the end of your next turn, you have resistance to all damage.

### Mantle of the Fallen Crusader
*3rd-level evocation*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 Action
- **Range:** Self
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___

Unholy power radiates from you in an aura with a 30-foot radius. Until the spell ends, the aura moves with you, centered on you. While in the aura, each enemy creature takes an additional 1d4 necrotic damage when it is hit with a weapon attack.

### Mass Compelled Duel
*5th-level enchantment*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 bonus action
- **Range:** 60 feet
- **Components:** V
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 minute
___

You issue a challenge, demanding that a number of creatures attack you and you alone.

Choose up to six creatures in range. Each must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the creature is drawn to you, compelled by your demand. For the duration, it has disadvantage on attack rolls against creatures other than you, and must make a Wisdom saving throw each time it attempts to move to a space that is more than 30 feet away from you; if it succeeds on this saving throw, this spell doesn’t restrict the target’s movement for that turn.

The spell effect ends on a creature if a creature friendly to you damages the target or casts a harmful spell on it, or if you end your turn more than 60 feet away from the target.

\columnbreak

### Mass Inflict Wounds
*5th-level Necromancy*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 60 feet
- **Comnponents:** V, S
- **Duration:** Instantaneous
___

A wave of necrotic energy washes out from a point of your choice within range.

Choose up to six creatures in a 30-foot-radius sphere centered on that point. Each target must make a Constitution save or take 5d10 necrotic damage. On a success, they take half damage. 

***At higher level.*** When you cast this spell using a spell slot of 6th level or higher, the damage increases by 1d10 for each slot level above 5th.

### Path of Ice
*3rd-level transmutation*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 30 feet
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** 1 hour
___

You let out an aura that freezes the ground around you. Creatures in range that you choose can walk on water as if it were solid; no more than 10 creatures other than you can benefit from this at a time.

Additionally, ground in a 10 foot radius around you becomes difficult terrain, covered in ice. 

### Remorseless Winter
*5th-level evocation*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** Self (40 foot radius)
- **Components:** V, M (a glass sphere filled with water and flecks of silver worth at least 200gp)
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes
___

Until the spell ends, icy winds swirl in a 20-foot-tall cylinder with a 40-foot radius centered on you. The area is heavily obscured, and exposed flames in the area are doused.

The wind constantly batters creatures within it to the ground, making it into difficult terrain and deafening any creatures within the area. When a creature enters the spell's area for the first time on a turn or starts its turn there, it must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, it takes 5d10 cold damage, falls prone and is restrained until the start of your next turn. On a successful save, it takes half damage and no other effects.

\pagebreakNum

### Unholy Frenzy
*3rd-level abjuration*
___
- **Casting Time:** 1 action
- **Range:** 40 feet
- **Components:** V, S, M (a small skull or voodoo doll)
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 10 minutes
___

[Choose a creature you can see within range. You infuse its mind and body with death energy, sending it into a killing frenzy. The target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, the target goes into a frenzy for the duration of the spell.

While in a frenzy, the creature must use its movement to move towards any creature it can see that it can reach this turn if possible, and then use its action to attack that creature. It cannot cast spells or maintain concentration on any spell except this one while in a frenzy, and it cannot choose not to kill a creature that it reduces to 0 hit points.

For the duration of the spell, whether or not the target failed its saving throw, its body is infused with unholy power. The creature’s melee weapon attacks deal extra damage equal to your Charisma modifier, and whenever it uses the Attack action, it makes one more attack than usual. At the start of each of its turns, it takes 2d6 necrotic damage. This damage can’t be reduced or prevented in any way.

### Unholy Weapon
*5th-level Evocation*
___
- **Casting time:** 1 Bonus Action
- **Range:** Touch
- **Components:** V, S
- **Duration:** Concentration, up to 1 hour

You imbue a weapon you touch with unholy power. Until the spell ends, the weapon draws light into itself, causing magical darkness in a 30—foot radius and lowering illumination by a step for an additional 30 feet. While you hold the weapon, you can see through this darkness.

In addition, weapon attacks made with it deal an extra 2d8 necrotic damage on a hit. If the weapon isn’t already a magic weapon, it becomes one for the duration. As a bonus action on your turn, you can dismiss this spell and cause the weapon to spread the darkness out, causing it to cling to creatures. Each creature of your choice that you can see within 30 feet ofyou must make a Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes 4d8 necrotic damage, and it is blinded for 1 minute. On a successful save, a creature takes half as much damage and isn’t blinded. At the end of each Ofits turns, a blinded creature can make a Constitution saving throw, ending the effect on itself on a success.


\pagebreakNum

# Appendix

## New Background: 
### Knight of the Ebon Blade

___
___
***“All that I am: anger, cruelty, vengeance - I bestow upon you, my chosen knight. I have granted you immortality so that you may herald in a new, dark age for the Scourge.”***
 
— The Lich King's first words to a new death knight.
___

You belong to the Knights of the Ebon Blade, the order of renegade death knights. Originally created as members of the Scourge under the direct command of the Lich King, they were intended for use as sacrificial pawns to take down a powerful paladin and opponent of the Lich King. Yet instead they were turned into a weapon against the Scourge.

As a member of their order you are probably one of their death knights. The death knights of the floating fortress of Acherus were once great warriors and paladins who had died before being resurrected by the Lich King as his instruments of death. Yet not all who are part of the order are the undead fighters. Former members of the Scourge, warriors seeking to gain the power of the death knights, and honorary members of other factions all make up the ranks of the Ebon Blade.
___
- **Skill Proficiencies:** Arcana, Intimidation
- **Tool Proficiencies:** Smith's Tools
- **Languages:** One of your choice
- **Equipment:** A signet denoting your membership, a trinket of your past (a ring, brooch, a yellowed and faded love letter, lock of a loved one's hair, etc.), a set of travelers clothes, and a belt pouch with 10 gp.
___

#### Feature: Fellow Outcast

Death knights and those who associate with them are almost universally reviled. Those who have distinguished themselves as great heroes may receive recognition, but most will find that people fear and hate them just for their existence. However this does come with a silver lining. 

As an officially neutral organization, the Knights of the Ebon Blade exist outside of the normal Alliance-Horde war. While they will almost never go directly against their race and faction, some fellow members of the order can be convinced to give more consideration to a fellow order member than to their faction, providing information and material aid.

Additionally, you have knowledge of the sigil sequence needed to access the permanent teleporation circle located in Acherus, the Ebon Hold. 

#### Suggested Characteristics

Members of the Ebon Blade are often gruff and sometimes cruel, as a result of their dark lifestyle and urges. Memories of a past life can sometimes temper this, but death knights as a whole tend to be a self-interested lot. One thing they all have in common: a burning hatred of the Scourge.

**d8**|**Personality Trait**
--|:---
1|I will outlive these mere mortals around me.
2|I'm cruel and selfish.
3|I take great joy in torture, and often keep reminders of those I have killed.
4|I show little care for those who I deem weak.
5|I'm apathetic all the time
6|My fate is grim, thus I am inclined to save others from theirs.
7|I experienced death, and I fear it. Because of this, I'm a coward.
8|I want to destroy mankind with an undead army.

**d6**|**Ideal**
--|:---
1|**Selfishness.** I benefit myself, it's every man for himself out here. (Chaotic)
2|**Repentant.** I cannot possibly undo the wrongs I have done, but I can still try and atone. (Good)
3|**Survival.** The shadow will devour all that exists, but it will consume me last of all. (Neutral)
4|**Vengeance.** I was brought into a world that hates and fears me. Those responsible for my suffering must pay. (Evil)
5|**Zealotry.** My eternal enemy – the Scourge – must be hunted and eradicated. All tasks must lead towards this goal. (Any)
6|**Honor.** I may fall, but my Honor is eternal. (Lawful)

**d6**|**Bond**
--|:---
1|I am heartless and I am cold. Yet, it does not mean I do not care.
2|There is no sacrifice I will not make to uphold my honor.
3|I will find redemption, even if it costs me everything.
4|I do not form alliances easily, and trust slowly.
5|I had a friend when I was alive, and I want to know what happened to them.
6|Being feared and hated by all has taught me to rely only on myself.

**d6**|**Flaw**
--|:---
1|I am particularly fearful of death, as I know to where I would return. As a result I can be cowardly or paranoid.
2|I'm used to commanding the unquestioning dead, human interaction confuses me.
3|Some might call me fearless, in reality, I simply lack self preservation instincts.
4|I tire of the world, and find no joy in things.
5|I find causing pain to others a little too enjoyable for most people's tastes.
6|I was once hero, yet how far I've fallen. I can trust no one, not even myself.

\pagebreakNum


## New Items

### Greatsword of the Ebon Blade

<img src='https://gamepedia.cursecdn.com/wowpedia/b/b6/Greatsword_of_the_Ebon_Blade_TCG.jpg?version=54e88d87b1646091835ad0e262fa32db' style='width:325px' />

> *The greatest instrument of vengeance for the Knights of the Ebon Blade.*

*Weapon (greatsword), rare (requires attunement)*

This weapon is made entirely of saronite. Taking advantage of the fact that saronite weighs a quarter of normal steel, this weapon is four times as large as a normal greatsword of its type. The wide blade can be a boon to those who fight defensively, allowing a person proficient in the greatsword to receive a +2 bonus to Armor Class when using the Dodge action. 

The incredible strength of saronite allows this weapon to function as an adamantine weapon, and any attack against an object is treated as a critical hit.

For death knights however, the weapon provides a special benefit. When a death knight is attuned to the weapon and using it as a runeblade, they can apply their Improved Runeblade runic empowerment without having it count against the maximum number of active runes.

***Cursed.*** As a saronite item, the greatsword carries the **Curse of Yogg-Saron**, as noted in the sidebar.

\columnbreak

### Greathelm of the Scourge Champion

<img src='https://gamepedia.cursecdn.com/wowpedia/d/d9/Greathelm_of_the_Scourge_Champion_TCG.jpg?version=3c5ab041249b20aecb8041aa4534829e' style='width:325px' />

> *Bestowed by the Lich King on those who willingly spread the disease of undeath.*

*Wondrous item, rare (requires attunement)*

When attuned to this item, you have the Undead Fortitude ability.

___
> ### Curse of Yogg-Saron
> 
> Items made of saronite whisper in the minds of those that carry them, slowly driving them insane. Unless an item is sealed in a lead-lined box or kept at a distance, those who spend at least 1 minute carrying, wearing, or wielding the item must make a DC 13 Charisma save at the end of their next long rest. Failure causes 1 point of Wisdom damage, which lasts until removed by magic such as _greater restoration_. 
>
> If your Charisma is reduced to 0 as a result of this damage, you become permanently insane, as you seek out the Master who whispers in your mind. Once you reach this state, nothing less than a _miracle_ can cure your mind.
>
> Undead and Death Knights have shown a remarkable resistance to this effect and can use the item normally without having to make Charisma saves, though the whispers remain.

\pagebreakNum

### Runed Soulblade

<img src='https://gamepedia.cursecdn.com/wowpedia/thumb/9/98/Runed_Soulblade_TCG.jpg/450px-Runed_Soulblade_TCG.jpg?version=67cdf7ef280b8ab8daca2b2a893dc632' style=width:325px />

> *"Forged in the fires of Acherus, these runeblades now serve the Horde and the Alliance."*

*Weapon (greatsword or longsword), common*

An important ingredient in the ritual to create a death knight, the creation of a runed soulblade requires the death of an intelligent being, whose soul quenches the blade and turns it into a vessel for runic power. 

\pagebreakNum

<img src='https://gamepedia.cursecdn.com/wowpedia/8/8e/Gargoyle_TCG.jpg?version=6cd9c3ee51263aa6fbb4dff20062811c' style='width:325px' />

> “Out of nowhere, he was grabbed by stony talons and whisked away into the night sky...”
> 
> — Commander Falstaav'

___
> ## Gargoyle
> *Medium monstrosity, chaotic evil*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 15 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 45 (6d8 + 18)
> - **Speed** 30 ft., fly 50 ft.
> ___
> STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA
> ---|---|---|---|---|---
> 15(+2)|11(+0)|16(+3)|5(-3)|11(+0)|7(-2)
> ___
> - **Damage Resistances** bludgeoning, piercing, and slashing from non magical attacks that aren't adamantine
> - **Damage Immunities** poison
> - **Condition Immunities** exhaustion, petrified, poisoned
> - **Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 10
> - **Languages** understands Common but can't speak
> - **Challenge** 2 (450 XP)
> 
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The gargoyle makes two attacks: one with its bite and one with its claws. 
> 
> ***Bite.*** Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 5 (1d6 + 2) piercing damage.
> 
> ***Claws.*** Melee Weapon Attack: +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 9 (2d6 + 2) piercing damage.
> 
> ***Stone Form.*** The gargoyle turns itself to stone making it indistinguishable from an inanimate statue. While it is turned this way, the gargoyle can't take any actions or move, and regains 5 hit points at the end of each of its turns. The gargoyle can turn itself into flesh using its bonus action.

\columnbreak

<img src='https://gamepedia.cursecdn.com/wowpedia/3/3e/Raise_Dead_TCG.jpg' style='width:325px' />

___
> ## Lesser Ghoul
> *Medium undead, chaotic evil*
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 12
> -  **Hit Points** 18 (4d8)
> - **Speed 30 ft.
> ___
> STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA
> ---|---|---|---|---|---
> 13(+1)|15(+2)|10(+0)|7(-2)|10(+0)|6(-2)
> ___
> - **Damage Immunities** poison
> - **Condition Immunities** charmed, exhausted, poisoned
> - **Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 10
> - **Languages** Understands language of its creator but cannot speak
> - **Challenge** 1/2 (100 XP)
> ___
> **Undead Fortitude** If damage reduces the ghoul to 0 hit points, it must make a Constitution saving throw with a DC of 5+the damage taken, unless the damage is radiant or from a critical hit. On a success, the ghoul drops to 1 hit point instead. The ghoul makes the save as if it is proficient in Constitution saving throws.
> ___
> ### Actions
> ***Claws*** *Melee Weapon Attack:* +4 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. *Hit:* 7 (1d6 + 2) slashing damage.
> 
> ***Cannibalize (Recharge after a Short or Long Rest)*** The ghoul cannibalizes the corpse of a humanoid that has been dead for less than a day, regaining 10 hit points. Each creature of the ghoul's choice that is within 30 feet of the ghoul and can see it must make a DC 12 Wisdom saving throw or become frightened for 1 minute. A creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success. If a creature's save is successful or the effect ends for it, the creature is immune to any ghoul's cannibalize for the next 24 hours.

\pagebreakNum

___
> ## Plague Eruptor
> *Large undead, chaotic evil*
> 
> ___
> - **Armor Class** 15 (natural armor)
> - **Hit Points** 94 (9d10 + 45)
> - **Speed** 60 ft.
> ___
> STR|DEX|CON|INT|WIS|CHA
> --|--|--|--|--|--
> 18(+4)|13(+1)|20(+5)|7(-2)|9(-1)|7(-2)
> ___
> **Skills** Perception +2
> **Damage Immunities** poison
> **Condition Immunities** poisoned
> **Senses** darkvision 60 ft., passive Perception 12
> **Languages** --
> **Challenge** 7 (2,900 XP)
> ___
> ***Poison Splash.*** When the plague eruptor takes damage of any type but psychic, each creature within 5 feet of it takes 9 (2d8) poison damage.
> 
> ***Regeneration.*** The plague eruptor regains 10 hit points at the start of each of its turns. If the plague eruptor takes radiant damage, this trait doesn't function at the start of its next turn. The plague eruptor dies only if it starts its turn with 0 hit points and doesn't regenerate.
>
> ***Stench.*** Any creature that starts its turn within 10 feet of the plague eruptor must succeed on a DC 14 Constitution saving throw or be poisoned until the start of the creature's next turn. On a successful saving throw, the creature is immune to the stench of all plague eruptors for 1 minute.
>
> ### Actions
> ***Multiattack.*** The plague eruptor makes three attacks: one with its bite and two with its slams.
> 
> ***Bite.*** Melee Weapon Attack: +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 7 (1d6 + 4) piercing damage plus 4 (1d8) poison damage, and the creature is poisoned until the start of the plague eruptor's next turn.
> 
> ***Slam.*** Melee Weapon Attack: +7 to hit, reach 5 ft., one target. Hit: 11 (2d6 + 4) bludgeoning damage plus 4 (1d8) poison damage.
> 
> ***Popping Pustule (Recharge 6).*** One of the venomous pustules on the plague erutor bursts, releasing a spray of poison in a 15-foot cube. Each creature in the area must make a DC 16 Constitution saving throw. On a failed save, a creature takes 18 (4d8) poison damage and is poisoned for 1 minute. On a successful save, the creature takes half as much damage and isn't poisoned. A poisoned creature can repeat the saving throw at the end of each of its turns, ending the effect on itself on a success.

